<br>
Old world zones like ghost towns, the ability to get a pickup group is severly diminished, the word &quot;twink&quot; has completely been redefined, and the majority of the time I'm logged in is spent staring at the floor in a zone with 300+ people in it all trying to sell their stuff, high end content is only playable with a good 3 hour block of time and requires at least 11 (and most often more) other people, most often spending those 3 hours getting no loot and almost no XP.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong I still love this game, sure you can grab a group with a few other people and grind in PoP, but most likely you'll need a slower.  For the next expansion I'd like to see an old world revamp.  There are so many zones now making the world even larger would be stupid.  A nice large patch and update old zones.  Possibly like a intro to EQ2, have freeport become more corrupt, update kunark and antonica story lines, definitely update veeshan's peak, everyone getting new epics, dragons are older now and more fierce, make the sleeper an actual mob, etc. you get the idea.<br>
<br>
The trouble is that it would be impossible to do this without making some part of it purchasable(not impossible to me but impossible for them to even think about doing it without some sort of profit.)  They can't update the old world and have some people playing in the old kunark and some people playing in the new kunark.  They would have to probably &quot;nail&quot; every consumer with either a one time fee for the expansion or make a kunark unaccessable until you buy the new kunark.  They fixed a large part of travel issues with PoP and the books.  It would make something old new again, I think that this may be what they have in mind for EQ2, therefore they aren't going to do it.  Seriously though, there are far too many zones that are completely empty and almost a complete waste of software.<br>
<br>
Anyone have any thoughts on this?<br>
<br>
